
STRİNG
- we use it for represents of characters.
- it comes from java.lang package
- string is immutable. if we create an object once, it could not be changed or modified.

- create 2 way
1- string literal

String a = "poll";
String b = "poll";

when we create a, there is a "poll" object in string poll in java heap.
and we dont create new object for b,
a and b same object ind string poll. there is one object

2- by new keyword
String a2 = "java";
String b2 = new String("java");

a2 is created in java heap in String poll and b2 is created in java heap.
there are 2 object

- every character in string has index number.
index number starts from 0

- some methods:
1. charAt(index)= returns the character at the given index.
String name = "İrem";
name.charAt(1) = 'r';

2. length()= returns the total number of characters(it starts from 1)
name.length() = 4;

3. toLowerCase() = returns the new string which all chars are lower
   toUpperCase() = returns the new string which all chars are upper

4. equals()= check if two string have same text, returns boolean

5. trim() = returns new string without including the white spaces(unused spaces)

6. indexOf(str)= returns the index number of first occured character. returns int

7. lastIndexOf(str) = returns the index number of last occured character. returns int

8. replace(oldValue, newValue) = returns new string by replacing all old values with new values

9. replaceFirst(oldValue, newValue) = returns new string by replacing the FIRST MATHCING WITH given old value with new value.

10. substring(beginingIndex, endingIndex) = creates substring starting from the given beginning index till the given index(endingIndex is excluded)

11. substring(beginingIndex) =  creates substring starting from the given beginning index to end of the string

